					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The &quot;major updates&quot; tend to be pushed through but it does pop up a large window for the download that you can tell it &quot;not now&quot;. However there was recently a massive flaw found in ALL CPUs, particularly Intel CPUs that NEEDS to be patched and then a bunch of updates to help mitigate the performance costs of said fixes. And if you are a person who always does &quot;not now&quot; it eventually gets to the point where it realizes you don't know what is good for you and applies it. Really the updates on Windows are good things, and good for you. Unlike OSX where an update will usually uninstall 3 things and break 10 programs you where using <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /></div>

